        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 7:46PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 746 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
4 Bears Lodge, or 26 miles south of Stanley, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Town, Van Hook Park, 4 Bears Lodge, Four Bears Village, and Crow
Flies High State Recreation Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
northwestern North Dakota.</instruction>
